<div>
    <h2>Community Standards for Agience Preview</h2>

    <p>The Agience Preview community is built on collaboration, innovation, and mutual respect. These standards apply to all users, developers, and contributors who interact with the platform. By participating in Agience Preview, you agree to adhere to these standards:</p>

    <h3>1. <strong>Respectful Communication</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>All users are expected to engage in respectful and constructive communication.</li>
        <li>Harassment, bullying, hate speech, or discriminatory behavior of any kind will not be tolerated.</li>
        <li>Personal attacks, threats, or abuse directed at other users, developers, or the Agience team are strictly prohibited.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. <strong>Quality and Integrity of Contributions</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Users contributing functions, content, or other resources to the Agience Preview platform must ensure that their contributions are of high quality, reliable, and free from harmful or malicious intent.</li>
        <li>Contributions must be original or properly licensed. Do not submit plagiarized or stolen code, data, or other materials.</li>
        <li>It is essential that all contributions align with legal standards and do not violate any intellectual property rights or applicable laws.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. <strong>Prohibited Content</strong></h3>
    <p>The following types of content are strictly prohibited:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Harmful, illegal, or malicious content, including viruses, malware, or other types of disruptive software.</li>
        <li>Offensive, inflammatory, or inappropriate content, including but not limited to hate speech, obscene or defamatory material.</li>
        <li>Misinformation, misleading content, or attempts to deceive or manipulate other users.</li>
        <li>Content that violates any laws, regulations, or third-party rights (e.g., intellectual property, privacy rights).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. <strong>Monitoring and Enforcement</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Ikailo Inc. reserves the right to monitor all content shared on the platform to ensure compliance with these community standards.</li>
        <li>Any content or functionality that violates these standards may be removed without notice.</li>
        <li>Users found to be in violation of the community standards may have their access suspended or terminated at the discretion of Ikailo Inc.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. <strong>Reporting Violations</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>If you encounter behavior or content that violates these community standards, please report it immediately by <a href="/Contact">contacting the Agience support team.</a></li>
        <li>Reports will be reviewed, and appropriate action will be taken based on the severity of the violation.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>6. <strong>Consequences of Violations</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>
            Violations of the community standards may result in actions including but not limited to:
            <ul>
                <li>Removal of content or functionality.</li>
                <li>Temporary suspension or permanent termination of access to Agience Preview.</li>
                <li>Legal action in severe cases involving unlawful behavior or violation of third-party rights.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7. <strong>Contributing Responsibly</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>When contributing to the platform, ensure that your submissions meet the community’s quality expectations.</li>
        <li>Contributions that are poorly designed, buggy, or intentionally disruptive will be removed, and repeated violations will result in suspension.</li>
        <li>Collaborative contributions are encouraged, but ensure that you credit any co-contributors appropriately.</li>
    </ul>
</div>